FilmArray RP detected the pathogens in 28 patients (56%), namely, Influenza virus (n = 14, 28%), Respiratory syncytial virus (n = 6, 12%), and Human Rhinovirus (n = 6, 12%) (Table 3
). Two viruses were detected in two patients: Influenza virus and Respiratory syncytial virus and Influenza virus and Human rhinovirus. When the FilmArray RP results were arranged in time series (Fig. 1
), Respiratory syncytial virus, Human rhinovirus, and Coronavirus were observed during the influenza epidemics (from January 17 to February 27).
